  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">UN Joint-Project to Address Cooking Fuel Needs, Environmental Degradation and Food Security for Populations Affected by the Refugee Crisis</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project is implemented by the Food and Agriculture Organization, International Organization for Migration, and the World Food Programme, with the primary aim of contributing to the overall food and nutrition security, empowerment and resilience of Rohingya refugee and host community households in Cox&apos;s Bazar, Bangladesh. The programme has four main objectives, the first of which is to address the urgent cooking fuel needs of the Rohingya and host communities by providing liquid petroleum gas, thereby contributing to the overall food and nutrition security, capacity building and resilience of targeted beneficiaries. The second objective focuses on livelihoods activities for host communities-strengthening social cohesion, livelihoods and income generation for the heavily impacted host community through training and input provision. The third objective aims to reduce negative environmental impacts through land/forest rehabilitation. The fourth objective aims at increasing income generation by increasing agricultural production and marketing.</narrative>
  </description>
